<div id="comment_64265340" class="cw">
	<div id="comment_top_64265340" class="commentTop newcomment">
		<div class="title">
			<h4><a id="comment_link_64265340" name="comment_link_64265340" href="//science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23236682&amp;cid=64265340" onclick="return D2.setFocusComment(64265340)" >Re:Air pollution</a>


		 	<span id="comment_score_64265340" class="score"> (<a href="#" onclick="getModalPrefs('modcommentlog', 'Moderation Comment Log', 64265340); return false"><span class=opt>Score:</span>4</a>, Interesting)</span></h4>
		</div>
		<div class="details">
			<span class="by"><span class="byby">by </span><a href="//slashdot.org/~data+oyster">data oyster</a>  <span class="uid"><a href="//slashdot.org/~data+oyster">( 10309165 )</a></span></a></span><span class="writes" style="display:none"> writes:</span> 
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_64265340">		
		on Saturday February 24, 2024 @09:51AM (<span class="ind"></span><a href="//science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=23236682&amp;cid=64265340">#64265340</a>)
		<small> </small>
</span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_64265340">I worked in public health/environmental chemistry for a dozen years in the LA area in the 80s/90s, including getting trained by some of the most excellent US air pollution bureaucracy of the time.  A few points that I learned, draw your own conclusions:

1.  Always have your car A/C on recirculate while driving in polluted air. Cabin air filter will help you.
2.  If you see the brown-red bands of pollution on the horizon, that means you are in the pollution.
3.  A very high percentage of heart attacks occur within the 20 minutes after a commute.

-----
Complicating it all beyond simple toxic effects on the circulatory system are the facts that very small molecules like CO and NO are physiologically active at doses hundreds or thousand times lower than the first observable toxic levels.  So there is a ton we still don't know, many interactions.</div>
	</div>

	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_64265340">
